 tangent microbundle of M. This in turn is converted to the homotopy problem of classifying maps from M into a certain space PL/O. The set of equivalence classes of smoothings on M is given a natural abelian group structure.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aManifolds (Mathematics). 0aPiecewise linear topology. 7aMATHEMATICS / Linear & Nonlinear Programming.2bisacsh  aAffine transformation.  aApproximation.  aAssociative property.  aBijection.  aBundle map.  aClassification theorem.  aCodimension.  aCoefficient.  aCohomology.  aCommutative property.  aComputation.  aConvex cone.  aConvolution.  aCorollary.  aCounterexample.  aDiffeomorphism.  aDifferentiable function.  aDifferentiable manifold.  aDifferential structure.  aDimension.  aDirect proof.  aDivision by zero.  aEmbedding.  aEmpty set.  aEquivalence class.  aEquivalence relation.  aEuclidean space.  aExistential quantification.  aExponential map (Lie theory).  aFiber bundle.  aFibration.  aFunctor.  aGrassmannian.  aH-space.  aHomeomorphism.  aHomotopy.  aIntegral curve.  aInverse problem.  aIsomorphism class.  aK0.  aLinearization.  aManifold.  aMathematical induction.  aMilnor conjecture.  aNatural transformation.  aNeighbourhood (mathematics).  aNormal bundle.  aObstruction theory.  aOpen set.  aPartition of unity.  aPiecewise linear.  aPolyhedron.  aReflexive relation.  aRegular map (graph theory).  aSheaf (mathematics).  aSmoothing.  aSmoothness.  aSpecial case.  aSubmanifold.  aTangent bundle.  aTangent vector.  aTheorem.  aTopological manifold.  aTopological space.  aTopology.  aTransition function.  aTransitive relation.  aVector bundle.  aVector field.1 aHirsch, Morris W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/